{"key":"post-13676810","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13676810</id>\n<content>I think rather than trying to reinvent the wheel, you should use the site search feature and type in mini-greenhouse or greenhouse, or greenhouse tek, etc., and look at all the thousands before who have worked through all the bugs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It's very common for new growers to think humidity is the most important facet of mushroom growing, when in fact it's the supply of fresh air that is paramount.&amp;nbsp; You need to have high humidity and lots of fresh air.&amp;nbsp; You'll want a cool mist humidifier inside.&amp;nbsp; Perlite trays are fine for catching drips and 'helping' slightly with humidity, but they won't be enough.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13680704</next>\n<prev>13674977</prev>\n<first>13674335</first>\n<last>13682559</last>\n<when>1293156311</when>\n<utime>12/24/10 04:05 AM</utime>\n</post>"}